'''Robert A. Martin''' (born November 14, 1953) is a former [[American football]] [[linebacker]] who played four seasons in the [[National Football League]] with the [[New York Jets]] and [[San Francisco 49ers]]. He was drafted by the New York Jets in the sixth round of the [[1976 NFL Draft]]. He played [[college football]] at the [[University of Nebraska<U+2013>Lincoln]] and attended David City High School in [[David City, Nebraska]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.profootballarchives.com/mart01400.html | title=BOB MARTIN | publisher=profootballarchives.com | accessdate=November 25, 2014}}</ref>


